The paper discusses market fairness, transparency, and manipulation in electronic trading, which are topics that fall under game theory (cs.GT) and trust and reputation (cs.TR). The paper also addresses technical shortcomings and infrastructure complexities, which are relevant to computer networks and communications (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), and systems and control (cs.SI).
